{
  "texts": [
    "Strategically combining methods will allow assessing if the DSA achieves its aims around transparency, accountability and empowering users.",
    "Overview of research needs and objectivesThe current goal is to produce detailed evidence on the DSA's performance and areas for improvement, enabling systematic enhancements to better achieve its aims of protecting the public.",
    "To do so, it's vital to ensure assessment methods directly related to DSA's operational mechanisms, aiding in strategic updates that are informed by solid, actionable insights throughout its deployment.We define three main types of methods.",
    "Quantitative techniques facilitate assessing phase-in outcomes related to advertising transparency, policy impacts on moderation consistency, and tracing notice-and-takedown efficacy (Code: AT, NTD, DD).",
    "Qualitative analyses provide equally vital contextualization regarding governance adaptations during high-risk events and platform discourses on evolving responsibilities (Code: AD, RA)."
  ]
}